gurmukhi: Aaur rqn niRp Dwm quA qiRAw rqn qy hIn ]
transliteration: Aur Rattan Nrip Dhaam Tua Triaa Rattan Te Hoon||
translation: “O king, Thou hast all other gems except the gem of wife;

gurmukhi: bDU eyk bn mY bsY iqh qum bro pRbIn ]86]
transliteration: Badhoo Ek Ban Mai Basai Tih Toum Bado Praboon||86||
translation: “One beautiful woman lives in the forest, O adept one, marry her.”86.

gurmukhi: sunI mnohir bwq niRp bUiJE pRin qwih ko ]
transliteration: Sounoo Manohar(i) Baat Nrip Boodheio Poun(i0 Taah(i) Ko||
translation: When the king heard these bewitching words, he said;

gurmukhi: mo so khIAY BRwq brnn qwih srIr ko ]87]
transliteration: Mo So Kahooai Bhraat Barnan Taah(i) Daroor Ko||87||
translation: “O brother, tell me, how she looks?”87.

gurmukhi: hir so muK hY hirqI duK hY AilkY hir hwr pRBw hrnI hY ]
transliteration: Har(i) So Moukh Hai Haritoo Doukh Hai Alikai Hair(i) Haar Prabhaa Harnoo Hai||
translation: “Her face is like the moon, seeing which all the sufferings are effaced; her curly hair even steal the beauty of snakes.

gurmukhi: locn hY hir sy srsy hir sy Bruty hir sI brunI hY ]
transliteration: Lochanndhai Har(i) Se Sarse Har(i) Se Bharoute Har(i) Soo Barounoo Hai||
translation: “Her eyes are like the blossomed lotus; her eyebrows are like bow and her eyelashes like arrows.

gurmukhi: kyhir so krhw clbo hir pY hir kI hrnI qrnI hY ]
transliteration: Kehar(i) So Kar-haa Chalbo Har(i0 Pai Har(i) Koo Harnoo Tarnoo Hai||
translation: “Her waist is slim like that of a lion, her gait is like that of an elephant and makes shyful the glory of the wife of Cupaid.

gurmukhi: hY kr mY hir pY hir soN hir rUp kIey hir kI DrnI hY ]88]
transliteration: Hai Kar Mai Har(i0 Pai Har(i0 Son Har(i0 Roop Kooe Har(i) Koo Dharnoo Hai||88||
translation: “She hath a sword in her hand and rides a lion; she is most magnificent like the sun the wife of god Shiva.88.

gurmukhi: mIn murJwny kMj KMjn iKswny Ail iPrq idvwny bn folY ijq iqq hI ]
transliteration: Moond Murjhaane Kanj Khanndan Khisaane Al(i) Phirat Divaane Ban Dolai Jit Tit Hoo||
translation: “Seeing the playfulness of the eyes, the big fish becomes shy, the tenderness makes the lotus shyful and the beauty makes the wagtail coy; considering the face as lotus, the black bees in their madness wander hither and thither in the forest.

gurmukhi: kIr Aau kpoq ibMb koklw klwpI bn lUty PUty iPrY mn cYn hUM n ikq hI ]
transliteration: Koor Au Kapot Binb Koklaa Kalaapoo Ban Loote Phoote Phirai Man Chain Hoon Na Kit Hoo||
translation: “Seeing the nose, the parrots and looking at the neck, the pigeons and haring the voice, the nightingale consider themselves robbed, their mind feels comfort nowhere.

gurmukhi: dwrm drk gieE pyK dsnin pwNq rUp hI kI kRwNq jg PYl rhI isq hI ]
transliteration: Daaram Darak Gado Pekh Dasanan(i0 Paant Roop Hoo Koo Kraant Jag Phail Rahoo Sit Hoo||
translation: “Seeing the row of teeth, the heart of pomegranate hath burst; the luster of her beauty is spreading like moonshine in the world.
